{"author":{"id":"daecaa79b752289d08fa06c7a65c8d0387caf00b7e262b5741f4805727d0a582"},"ops":[{"type":6,"timestamp":1747444625,"nonce":"3yR+C8ie47MWzVg/RFBlOenCFLw=","metadata":{"github-id":"UCE_lAHOCGKeh862_l2sznsFxoo"},"target":"cd7113e9f9f05a748dc31917af7f1b1a3528eb1b2a4086a8cd26ab3dee8cee4a","message":"this is obviously personal preference, but i far prefer a monospace font. right now, we hard-code the following font family:\n\n```\nfont-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\n```\n\nI think we could default to the system's `monospace` font instead of hard-coding this family. that is, replace it with:\n\n```\nfont-family: monospace;\n```\n\n... we could probably choose to ship a preferred font in the binary, or at least pull down from the web, if we wanted to. a good monospace font that is designed for improved readability, that i'm partial to, is [intel one mono](https://github.com/intel/intel-one-mono) (this is actually my system default, so i'm really not partial to whether or not we ship it or just default to the system monospace font).\n\n---\n\nthis is also something that could be configured by the user via a `git-bug.ui.web.fonts` git configuration prop in the future.","files":null},{"type":5,"timestamp":1747443618,"nonce":"rkIrUrtL9RWXgavvfjydcMfjuSA=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOCGKeh862_l2szwAAAAQewQGA"},"added":["area/ui/web"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1747443618,"nonce":"VP+ef+JThpRikVgsAR+q97jLu+U=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOCGKeh862_l2szwAAAAQewQGH"},"added":["kind/feature"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1747443618,"nonce":"KzD1FMmDot/mQw8h03TXrytP0Mo=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOCGKeh862_l2szwAAAAQewQGQ"},"added":["priority/backlog"],"removed":[]}]}